{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.39",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 39 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:1",
      "text": "Knowest thou the time when the wild goats bring forth among the rocks, or hast thou observed the hinds when they fawn?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:2",
      "text": "Hast thou numbered the months of their conceiving, or knowest thou the time when they bring forth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:3",
      "text": "They bow themselves to bring forth young, and they cast them, and send forth roarings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:4",
      "text": "Their young are weaned and go to feed: they go forth, and return not to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:5",
      "text": "Who hath sent out the wild ass free, and who hath loosed his bonds?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:6",
      "text": "To whom I have given a house in the wilderness, and his dwellings in the barren land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:7",
      "text": "He scorneth the multitude of the city, he heareth not the cry of the driver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:8",
      "text": "He looketh round about the mountains of his pasture, and seeketh for every green thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:9",
      "text": "Shall the rhinoceros be willing to serve thee, or will he stay at thy crib?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:10",
      "text": "Canst thou bind the rhinoceros with thy thong to plough, or will he break the clods of the valleys after thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:11",
      "text": "Wilt thou have confidence in his great strength, and leave thy labours to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:12",
      "text": "Wilt thou trust him that he will render thee the seed, and gather it into thy barnfloor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:13",
      "text": "The wing of the ostrich is like the wings of the heron, and of the hawk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:14",
      "text": "When she leaveth her eggs on the earth, thou perhaps wilt warm them in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:15",
      "text": "She forgetteth that the foot may tread upon them, or that the beasts of the field may break them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:16",
      "text": "She is hardened against her young ones, as though they were not hers, she hath laboured in vain, no fear constraining her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:17",
      "text": "For God hath deprived her of wisdom, neither hath he given her understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:18",
      "text": "When time shall be, she setteth up her wings on high: she scorneth the horse and his rider.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:19",
      "text": "Wilt thou give strength to the horse or clothe his neck with neighing?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:20",
      "text": "Wilt thou lift him up like the locusts? the glory of his nostrils is terror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:21",
      "text": "He breaketh up the earth with his hoof, he pranceth boldly, he goeth forward to meet armed men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:22",
      "text": "He despiseth fear, he turneth not his back to the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:23",
      "text": "Above him shall the quiver rattle, the spear and shield shall glitter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:24",
      "text": "Chasing and raging he swalloweth the ground, neither doth he make account when the noise of the trumpet soundeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:25",
      "text": "When he heareth the trumpet he saith: Ha, ha: he smelleth the battle afar off, the encouraging of the captains, and the shouting of the army.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:26",
      "text": "Doth the hawk wax feathered by thy wisdom, spreading her wings to the south?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:27",
      "text": "Will the eagle mount up at thy command, and make her nest in high places?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:28",
      "text": "She abideth among the rocks, and dwelleth among cragged flints, and stony hills, where there is no access.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:29",
      "text": "From thence she looketh for the prey, and her eyes behold afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:30",
      "text": "Her young ones shall suck up blood: and wheresoever the carcass shall be, she is immediately there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:31",
      "text": "And the Lord went on, and said to Job:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:32",
      "text": "Shall he that contendeth with God be so easily silenced? surely he that reproveth God, ought to answer him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:33",
      "text": "Then Job answered the Lord, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.34",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:34",
      "text": "What can I answer, who hath spoken inconsiderately? I will lay my hand upon my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.39.35",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:35",
      "text": "One thing I have spoken, which I wish I had not said: and another, to which I will add no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
